VERDICT: REJECTED

The implementation adds the dashboard button, modal, generator, clipboard/download actions, and the generated file is broadly self-contained, but it misses a core task requirement for per-breakpoint exports. When `responsiveMode === VERDICT: REJECTED
"per-breakpoint"`, the generator intentionally uses the desktop breakpoint as the only 
structural/runtime source and only changes visual CSS via media queries. That means visible units, labels, header/subheader, animation style, progress style, completion behavior, RTL/LTR direction, and timer/runtime settings do not adapt at tablet/mobile widths. The task explicitly requires per-breakpoint settings to be honored and the exported widget to match the dashboard preview for the chosen breakpoint(s), so documenting this as a warning does not make the requirement complete.

There are also visual parity concerns, notably circular progress styling: the exported circular track uses `separatorColor` with opacity, while the React dashboard uses `digitBackground` as the track color. This will visibly diverge for multiple themes/settings, although this is secondary to the per-breakpoint failure.

TypeScript check passes (`npm run check`).

Security: none observed at the threshold for rejection. The generator makes reasonable efforts to escape HTML/script JSON and sanitize CSS values.

Next actions:
1. Rework per-breakpoint export so the runtime can switch complete breakpoint configs by `matchMedia`/resize, including structural/rendered DOM changes where units, labels, header, direction, animation/progress style, and completion settings differ.
2. Align generated circular/linear/progress and digit markup/styles exactly with the React preview components.
